rComments: Very articulate, a lot of theoretical content for a 2000 level course but she's engaging to listen to and has a charming personality.
They give really good lectures, with plenty of class discussion and examples.  In-depth exam review is provided before exams, and the exams themselves are fair.  Would take the class again!

She speaks in a way that makes it nearly impossible to understand what she's saying & uses unnecessarily longconfusing terms to describe things. Genuinely nice person, but it feels like she's reading theory papers the whole lecture. Gives full review before exams, but grades quite tough (2 papers, midterm and final).
